  "body": " A cup of coffee has its temperature (in degrees Fahrenheit) at time given by the function , where time is measured in minutes.   Use a central difference with to estimate the value of .    What are the units on the value of that you computed in (a)? What is the practical meaning of the value of ?    Which do you expect to be greater: or ? Why?    Write a sentence that describes the behavior of the function on the time interval . How do you think its graph will look? Why?          .    The coffee's temperature is decreasing at about degrees per minute.     .    We expect to get closer and closer to as time goes on.         Using the central difference formula, we find that .    Since is measured in degrees Fahrenheit and in minutes, we have degrees F per minute. This means that at the instant , the temperature of the coffee is decreasing at an instantaneous rate of about degrees per minute. Said differently, in the next minute, we'd expect the temperature of the coffee to drop about degrees.    We expect the coffee's temperature to decrease quickly early on when the difference between its temperature and the surroundings is greatest, and as time goes on for the coffee's temperature to approach that of the surrounding room. Keeping in mind that is an always decreasing function so that is always negative, we observe that should be less (more negative) than . These observations can also be confirmed by plotting a graph of .    We have noted that is always negative, and that we expect to get closer and closer to as time goes on (that is, is increasing). As such, we expect to look something like the graph of . This is reasonable since is also an exponential function, is always negative, is always increasing, and approaches as increases.     "
